title: For Sale:  Bulk Dealer Discount - Hollow Spy Coins
postcontent:
We have a large quantity of Hollow Covert Coins in stock, so we're reaching
out to dealers and retailers with an established customer base in the "spy gear", privacy, security, travel and related niches.

It occurred to me that these would probably sell well as an impulse buy novelty item on a gun shop checkout counter.

Since our primary focus is marketplace e-commerce, this is a one-time bulk
discount offer.

Covert Coin Half Dollars - Up to 300 units at $12.63/unit 
Covert Coin Nickels - Up to 300 units at $14.75/unit
Covert Coin Quarters - Up to 200 units at $10.92/unit

These coins, based on the Cold War era hollow coins, are precision machined
from authentic US Mint circulation nickels, quarters, and half dollars. Each
unit includes an opening ring. The nickels and half dollars effectively conceal a micro SD card. Some of the quarters do as well, but we can't guarantee those. Retail prices are generally $22-30.

Background info:
During the Cold War, Spies from both the East and West used Hollow Coins to
ferry secret messages, suicide poisons, and microfilms undetected. On May
1st, 1960 U2 Pilot Gary Francis Powers was shot down over the Soviet Union
and taken captive. In his possession was a hollow silver dollar containing a
poisoned needle that was to be used to take his own life in such a
circumstance. For one reason or another, he did not use it and was held for
21 months by the Soviets. He was then exchanged for Soviet spy KGB Colonel
Vilyam Fisher (aka Rudolf Abel) at the Glienicke Bridge, in Berlin, Germany.
Colonel Fisher was also no stranger to hollow coins...his original capture
by the United States FBI was directly related to a hollow nickel that was
used to transport microfilm.

Please, feel free to contact me for more information.
